 \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9991143558729825, \"rank\": 0.0008753100538920477, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The explosive - if rain-sodden - celebration included a show-stopping (or starting) performances from the likes ofCeline Dion, Lady Gaga and heavy-metal band Gojira, and appearances from the likes of, uh,American rapper Snoop Dogg too.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.175037271244002e-33, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997819059571559, \"rank\": 0.00021723341463382768, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 597, \"end\": 607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for latest news on the Paris Olympics  Meanwhile, sporting icons Zinedine Zidane, Serena Williams and Rafael Nadal joined the procession to participate in the Olympic torch relay.\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More controversially, the opening event also saw a portrayal of Leonardo DaVinci's Last Supper - featuring a diverse line-up which included several drag artists among those dining at the iconic table.\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 890, \"end\": 898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.454295959486278e-19, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.9813834903920165e-24, \"text\": \"DaVinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This drew the ire of several commentators online, who likened the display of celebration and inclusivity to something out of 'Sodom and Gomorrah.'\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The portrayal of the scene came under fire as it aired, with Elon Musk commenting via X: 'This was extremely disrespectful to Christians.'\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9499107472570248, \"rank\": 0.04729900405770421, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, professional boxer Ryan Garcia also shared his thoughts, writing on Instagram: 'The Olympics needs to be boycotted now.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1346, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Garcia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Garcia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Garcia\"}, {\"begin\": 1395, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8435995025644297e-40, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can not disrespect religion in front of millions.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This ain't right no one watch.'\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was extremely disrespectful to Christians  OLYMPIC PERVERTS: The opening ceremony of the Paris games features drag queens mocking \\\"The Last Supper\\\" a bearded dude in a dress, a decapitated head singing a song and a Smurf wearing a thong.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9499107472570248, \"rank\": 0.04729900405770421, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1628, \"end\": 1633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.515437567705848e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the people of Sodom and Gomorrah would blush.#Olympicspic.twitter.com/ntJ3OLpWOK  Many viewers invoked Sodom and Gomorrah as they shared their thoughts, quoting Genesis 18:20 - 21 as they railed against the perceived disrespect to their religion.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1796, \"end\": 1801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\", \"score\": 0.9971519862477077, \"rank\": 0.0028561481014708957, \"text\": \"Sodom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\"}, {\"begin\": 1885, \"end\": 1890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\", \"score\": 0.9971519862477077, \"rank\": 0.0028561481014708957, \"text\": \"Sodom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\"}, {\"begin\": 1943, \"end\": 1950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Genesis\", \"score\": 0.999990726013296, \"rank\": 9.253932032306059e-06, \"text\": \"Genesis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Genesis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Genesis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'OLYMPIC PERVERTS,' screamed American commentator Todd Starnes on X, 'The opening ceremony of the Paris games features \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" a bearded dude in a dress, a decapitated head singing a song and a Smurf wearing a Thong.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997819059571559, \"rank\": 0.00021723341463382768, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2080, \"end\": 2092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Todd_Starnes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Todd Starnes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Todd_Starnes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Todd_Starnes\"}, {\"begin\": 2128, \"end\": 2133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.515437567705848e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the people of Sodom and Gomorrah would blush.'\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2309, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2277, \"end\": 2282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\", \"score\": 0.9971519862477077, \"rank\": 0.0028561481014708957, \"text\": \"Sodom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodom_and_Gomorrah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 'decapitated head' in question?\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A nod to Marie Antoinette, the last queen prior to the French revolution, who was sentenced to death by guillotine after trial in 1973.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2356, \"end\": 2372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.510162312395535e-36, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 2402, \"end\": 2419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French revolution\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This came as part of the heavy-metal band Gojira's performance (making them the first metal band to ever play at the Olympic Games), singing the French revolutionary song \\u00c7a Ira.\", \"from\": 2484, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2526, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.175037271244002e-33, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 2629, \"end\": 2635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9591308356533712, \"rank\": 0.04062183093513345, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This particular scene played out along the same river Seine embankment opposite the Conciergerie, where the queen was once held captive.\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2748, \"end\": 2760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7661217699044155e-39, \"text\": \"Conciergerie\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Headless Marie Antoinette is a brat,' commented CNN anchor Jake Tapper on X, as the performance aired.\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2812, \"end\": 2828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.510162312395535e-36, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 2851, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999999999613465, \"rank\": 3.8804550325654054e-11, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}, {\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Tapper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jake Tapper\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Tapper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Tapper\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nicknamed the 'Peter Pan of Theatre,' for his youthful looks, Thomas Jolly, 42, is the mind behind last night's entertainment\\u2026 and outrage.\", \"from\": 2907, \"to\": 3046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2922, \"end\": 2931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Pan\", \"score\": 0.9996866744094522, \"rank\": 0.0003134237940641854, \"text\": \"Peter Pan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Pan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Pan\"}, {\"begin\": 2969, \"end\": 2975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9991143558729825, \"rank\": 0.0008753100538920477, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Growing up in a tiny village in Normandy, the Queer actor, comedian and director founded his theatre company La Piccola Familia in 2006.\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3080, \"end\": 3088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy\", \"score\": 0.9997853557038711, \"rank\": 0.000211923003313677, \"text\": \"Normandy\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy\"}, {\"begin\": 3168, \"end\": 3175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mazda_Familia\", \"score\": 0.9999612560998268, \"rank\": 3.87454015402361e-05, \"text\": \"Familia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mazda_Familia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mazda_Familia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, he created a 24-hour long play based on Shakespeare's Henry VI trilogy and Richard III, which he titled H6R3.\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3235, \"end\": 3246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Shakespeare\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.165468963916729e-12, \"text\": \"Shakespeare\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Shakespeare\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Shakespeare\"}, {\"begin\": 3249, \"end\": 3257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_VI_of_England\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.985890240648662e-20, \"text\": \"Henry VI\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_VI_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_VI_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 3270, \"end\": 3281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_III_of_England\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7754710576802135e-34, \"text\": \"Richard III\", \"types\": [